#: ../../../library/array.rst:11
msgid ""
"This module defines an object type which can compactly represent an array of "
"basic values: characters, integers, floating-point numbers, complex "
"numbers.  Arrays are mutable :term:`sequence` types and behave very much "
"like lists, except that the type of objects stored in them is constrained.  "
"The type is specified at object creation time by using a :dfn:`type code`.  "
"The following type codes are defined:"
msgstr ""

